Dear Hiring Team,

I am excited to apply for the *Integration Engineer* role at *Sevita*. I bring 3+ years of backend and integration engineering experience, plus a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University, and I am motivated by Sevita's mission of delivering quality, community-based services that lead to growth and independence.

In my recent Software Engineer role at Sperse, I modernized legacy point-to-point integrations into a loosely coupled, event-driven architecture using *Confluent Kafka* (`topics`, `producers`, `consumers`, *Schema Registry*, and *Kafka Connect*), and delivered independently deployable micro services across 1,000+ platform endpoints. I also built and operated integration APIs in *Java*, *Python*, and *Node.js*, standardized service contracts, and partnered with DevOps and Cloud teams to deliver secure, fault-tolerant services through *CI/CD pipelines*, *Azure DevOps*, *Docker*, and *Kubernetes*. This work directly aligns with Sevita's core responsibilities around integration design, deployment, and reliability.

At Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic storage integration service using *Python*, *PostgreSQL*, and *Redis* across *Google Cloud Storage*, *S3*, and *MinIO*, and contributed to an IAM platform in *React*, *Spring Boot*, and *AWS* supporting 30+ applications with enterprise integration patterns and secure inter-service communication. I also maintain strong monitoring and troubleshooting discipline through *observability/logging* tooling (*Langfuse*, *LangSmith*) and collaborative, cross-functional delivery habits reinforced through technical workshops for 50+ engineers and students.

I am especially drawn to Sevita's focus on *integrity* and *respect*, and to your commitment to helping people live fuller, more independent lives through high-quality support. I would value the opportunity to contribute this integration engineering background to Sevita's mission and help scale reliable, event-driven services that support your teams and the individuals you serve. I can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration.

